from talking to you.

23:36.895 --> 23:39.329
My God, is that it?
They're directing people...

23:39.498 --> 23:41.489
<i>...not to talk to me?</i>

23:45.437 --> 23:50.739
l had to sign a confidentiality statement
where l'm liable financially if l....

23:50.909 --> 23:53.241
<i>With this new situation--
You know what?</i>

23:53.412 --> 23:56.006
The hell with everything!
So l lose my job.

23:56.181 --> 23:59.378
Wait, honey, l can't. ''Honey.'' Sorry.
My medical would lapse.

23:59.551 --> 24:02.520
l've gotta care for my baby.
Al still hasn't proposed....

24:02.688 --> 24:06.681
You won't lose your job, Annie, okay?
All right? Don't tell me anything.

24:07.493 --> 24:09.017
Sorry, boss.

24:10.496 --> 24:11.793
Thanks a lot.

24:13.098 --> 24:14.622
You have a good night, Annie.

24:16.268 --> 24:17.929
l am just dying for you.

24:18.137 --> 24:20.503
That's a little extreme.

24:21.206 --> 24:22.605
Just be nauseous for me.

24:24.042 --> 24:26.567
<i>Yeah. A little morning sick for me.</i>

24:26.745 --> 24:28.440
Not a problem.

24:51.303 --> 24:55.137
-Hello?
-Hi. Lisa. This is George.

24:55.641 --> 24:57.233
<i>George Madison.</i>

24:59.211 --> 25:03.648
l.... l'm not sure how to
further identify myself.

25:04.316 --> 25:06.216
<i>Your voice sounds a little familiar.</i>

25:06.385 --> 25:09.684
l made this incredibly stupid
phone call to you a few days ago.

25:09.855 --> 25:13.222
Oh, right. How you doing, George?

25:13.892 --> 25:15.655
Would you like to have dinner?

25:16.228 --> 25:18.822
<i>-But aren't you...?
-No, l am not.</i>

25:20.132 --> 25:22.362
-You see--
-You don't have to explain.

25:22.534 --> 25:25.332
l'm sort of seeing somebody,
but we can have a meal.

25:26.305 --> 25:28.034
<i>-When?
-Anytime.</i>

25:28.207 --> 25:29.231
<i>Tomorrow's clear.</i>

25:29.408 --> 25:31.205
<i>-Triplo Due?
-l'll meet you there.</i>

25:31.376 --> 25:35.244
<i>-lt's Triple Two in English.
-lt's gotta be early, 6:00. l'm in training.</i>

25:36.181 --> 25:39.082
Okay. So it's a d-- lt's a date.

25:39.251 --> 25:41.219
<i>-Okay.
-All right.</i>

25:41.386 --> 25:43.581
<i>-l have made a date.
-Bye.</i>

25:43.755 --> 25:45.313
Good night.

28:02.060 --> 28:04.153
Come on, come on.

28:19.144 --> 28:21.977
Georgie. George.

28:22.247 --> 28:24.306
-Let's go inside.
-l have a date.

28:24.483 --> 28:28.351
Date? Son, we are in
a rapidly evolving situation here.

28:28.520 --> 28:31.853
l must tell you, l was afraid
to use the telephone.

28:32.024 --> 28:33.218
Because?

28:33.392 --> 28:35.758
No. No, no. Don't tell me.

28:35.927 --> 28:39.363
l'm not ready to take on
anything that l can't handle.

28:39.531 --> 28:42.295
No, you know what?
l know exactly how to handle this.

28:42.467 --> 28:44.731
l'll treat myself
like a company in trouble.

28:44.903 --> 28:49.067
What l think is you are just indulging
in a lot of neuroses.

28:49.241 --> 28:52.176
You take on too much,
it becomes about how much...

28:52.344 --> 28:55.211
...instead of how well you handle it.
That applies now.

28:55.380 --> 28:56.574
-Stand still!
-No.

28:56.748 --> 28:59.308
You do not have the luxury
of not hearing this.

28:59.484 --> 29:01.918
Are you making me literally run
from bad news?

29:02.087 --> 29:04.817
The chickenshit board has dec--

29:10.695 --> 29:12.128
l gotta go. l have a date.

29:12.297 --> 29:14.231
What happened to you was horrific.

29:15.033 --> 29:17.160
-Stop acting tough.
-lt's the worst move!

29:17.335 --> 29:18.632
Look at the time.

29:18.804 --> 29:21.932
Hey, everybody, l have to leave.
l have a date.

29:22.107 --> 29:23.699
-What?
-Now, Lise?

29:23.875 --> 29:25.604
-Yeah.
-Lisa?

29:25.911 --> 29:27.037
Nobody's buying this.

29:27.212 --> 29:30.079
-We should protest!
-We should.

29:30.449 --> 29:32.440
Smalls, what do you want us to do?

29:32.617 --> 29:36.144
-Lisa.
-Okay. There is one thing.

29:36.321 --> 29:40.382
When l come to visit you at training
camp when you're getting ready...

29:40.559 --> 29:43.153
...just don't feel funny talking to me.

29:43.328 --> 29:46.786
Okay? Don't feel sad for me.

29:46.965 --> 29:50.765
Because my biggest fear is that
you won't be yourselves around me.

29:50.936 --> 29:54.770
l've seen that, and if that happened,
it would just make me feel like l--

29:54.940 --> 29:57.067
Like l didn't know you anymore.

29:57.242 --> 29:59.574
And l want to.

29:59.744 --> 30:01.871
l need to.

30:03.348 --> 30:05.009
Just say, ''Okay, Lisa.''

30:05.350 --> 30:07.477
Okay, Lisa.

30:07.986 --> 30:10.284
God. l--

30:10.455 --> 30:14.983
l gotta go. l gotta go.
He's waiting for me.

30:15.160 --> 30:17.094
-l love you.
-Love you. Love you.

30:17.262 --> 30:19.321
-Love you too.
-Go, Lise.

30:19.498 --> 30:21.557
-Go, Lise.
-Lise!

30:33.879 --> 30:35.346
-Hi.
-Name, please.

30:35.514 --> 30:37.209
l'm meeting George....

30:37.382 --> 30:40.943
-Madison?
-l'm not sure. l forget.

30:46.791 --> 30:49.316
Could that be him over there?

30:50.762 --> 30:52.491
l'll bet that is him.

30:53.031 --> 30:55.329
That's the sort of day l'm having.

30:56.501 --> 30:59.231
You don't have to take me.
Thank you, though.

31:06.077 --> 31:07.544
George?

31:08.613 --> 31:10.080
Are you George?

31:10.749 --> 31:12.774
l'm Lisa.

31:12.951 --> 31:15.749
-Very good of you to join me.
-Yeah.

31:17.355 --> 31:18.845
How you doing?

31:20.091 --> 31:21.786
How are you doing?

31:23.161 --> 31:24.219
l'm great.

31:24.930 --> 31:25.988
-Yeah?
-Yep.

31:26.164 --> 31:28.598
Well, treasure it.

31:31.403 --> 31:32.461
You okay?

31:32.637 --> 31:35.936
No. l'm sorry,
l'm not even aware that--

31:36.508 --> 31:41.070
l have to apologize. This might not
be the best first impression.

31:41.246 --> 31:43.476
l.... l had...

31:45.183 --> 31:47.674
...an unusual 2 4 hours.

31:47.852 --> 31:51.413
Okay. Well, the bad days
make the good ones better.

31:51.590 --> 31:53.114
So don't worry about it.

31:55.260 --> 31:57.057
ls this an ltalian restaurant?

31:57.229 --> 31:58.958
Yes, it's a very good one.

31:59.364 --> 32:00.626
Oh, yeah, it looks good.

32:00.999 --> 32:03.490
-Let's get a drink.
-None for me.

32:03.668 --> 32:07.195
You know what? You're right.
Yeah. l shouldn't drink.

32:07.372 --> 32:09.272
-Don't let me stop you.
-No, no, no.

32:09.441 --> 32:13.400
Believe me, drinking too much
two nights in a row could be a mistake.

32:15.814 --> 32:19.272
l haven't had anything since
lunch yesterday, so l'm starving.

32:20.452 --> 32:21.680
You don't drink at all?

32:21.853 --> 32:24.788
-l follow my father's rule on drinking.
-Which is?

32:24.956 --> 32:28.323
Never drink to feel better.
Only drink to feel even better.

32:29.261 --> 32:30.922
That's fantastic.

32:31.396 --> 32:32.920
Yep. lt's a good one.

32:33.098 --> 32:36.124
That's great.
But sometimes l think that...

32:36.301 --> 32:39.361
...one drink can give you
a little better perspective.

32:40.305 --> 32:42.671
Not for me.
l guess it depends on the person.

32:42.841 --> 32:47.244
Look, if you wanna have a drink,
have a drink. Keeping talking about it--

32:47.412 --> 32:50.973
l don't need permission to drink.
lf l want a drink, l'll order one.

32:51.149 --> 32:53.982
Jesus! Do you know
l don't know you?

32:54.252 --> 32:57.187
l'm sorry. l'm not good today.

32:58.056 --> 33:02.220
Maybe l should say what's going on.
l never talk about myself. l should.

33:02.494 --> 33:05.691
No! Don't do that.

33:07.399 --> 33:10.334
George, this is what l'm suggesting.
That we eat.

33:11.102 --> 33:14.299
And that we don't work
at this conversation.

33:14.472 --> 33:16.633
-Let's just cut ourselves a break...
-Yes.

33:16.808 --> 33:20.300
...and give ourselves permission
to be quiet.

33:20.478 --> 33:24.039
For the whole dinner.
Completely quiet.

33:26.418 --> 33:28.147
Can l talk to the waiter?

33:29.721 --> 33:32.815
As long as you don't tell him
about your day.

34:33.985 --> 34:36.545
l mean, that....

34:38.857 --> 34:41.052
That was just what l needed.

34:42.927 --> 34:44.985
You take care of yourself.

34:50.368 --> 34:53.098
l'm just leaving my place
to go to dinner.

34:53.271 --> 34:56.467
-Good evening, Mr. Madison. Taxi?
-Yes, thank you, Tom.

34:56.641 --> 34:59.804
Okay, Dad, l'm ready.
What happened?

34:59.978 --> 35:02.674
What if l come by later?
The phone isn't....

35:03.415 --> 35:07.511
Just tell me. l'd rather use the rest of
the night processing the information.

35:10.355 --> 35:16.021
l'm sorry, this is private.
There's still some privacy left.

35:18.096 --> 35:20.860
<i>The board is refusing to pay...</i>

35:21.032 --> 35:23.865
<i>-...your legal bills. Now--
-Hey.</i>

35:26.204 --> 35:27.933
l think l met a great girl.

35:29.340 --> 35:32.776
Oh, good. There is a God.

35:50.028 --> 35:52.997
The girls needed to tell you
how they felt.

35:53.164 --> 35:54.495
lt's something, isn't it?

35:54.899 --> 35:57.925
Last time l saw that was
when a kid died in high school...

35:58.102 --> 36:00.297
...and they left this stuff by the road.

36:00.472 --> 36:01.734
How about straight talk?

36:01.906 --> 36:04.807
l am very sensitive
to what you're going through.

36:05.176 --> 36:07.303
You know what you need most
right now?

36:07.579 --> 36:09.171
-Yes.
-What?

36:09.547 --> 36:11.344
lnsensitivity.

36:14.319 --> 36:15.843
Yeah?

36:16.955 --> 36:19.549
-Who is it?
-lt's Lisa.

36:19.724 --> 36:21.385
Could you narrow it down?

36:21.559 --> 36:22.560
l'm not kidding right now.

36:22.560 --> 36:23.925
l'm not kidding right now.

36:24.095 --> 36:28.088
A good Lisa. Come here. Get in.

36:32.136 --> 36:34.331
-You're alone, right?
-Yeah.

36:34.606 --> 36:37.074
l was just working up the night.

36:37.942 --> 36:39.307
Do you want me to be here?

36:41.279 --> 36:43.008
-Yes, l do.
-Okay.

36:43.181 --> 36:45.206
Then this is what l need.

36:45.383 --> 36:48.682
lf in the middle of the night
l start crying or...

36:48.853 --> 36:53.586
...shaking or acting enormously upset,
l don't want you to ask what's wrong.

36:53.758 --> 36:56.955
l want you to just ignore it.
ls that okay with you?

36:57.962 --> 37:00.556
-Actually, that's my preference.
-Okay, good.

37:02.233 --> 37:05.532
Have a seat. My game's coming up.

37:14.546 --> 37:17.413
<i>Matty Reynolds gets him.
The Nationals win.</i>

37:17.582 --> 37:19.846
-Good mechanics.
-Yeah.

37:29.193 --> 37:31.957
Okay. Let's go, l got it.

37:45.143 --> 37:47.008
Can you afford me?

37:47.946 --> 37:52.781
The firm is refusing to pay my legal
bills, but my father is willing to help.

37:52.951 --> 37:56.409
You can't take money from him,
not with his position on the board.

37:56.888 --> 37:58.515
What would your retainer be?

37:58.890 --> 38:04.328
Three hundred thousand, and another
three in escrow in case it goes to trial.

38:08.833 --> 38:11.597
-l suppose l could sell--
-Everything you can.

38:11.970 --> 38:13.528
Okay.

38:19.243 --> 38:21.370
-Sit down.
-l don't wanna lie down.

38:21.846 --> 38:24.144
-l said, ''Sit down.''
-l don't think you did.

38:24.315 --> 38:27.648
Yes, l did. l never ask someone
to lie down on a first visit.

38:28.786 --> 38:30.720
-Sorry.
-Okay.

38:37.328 --> 38:38.795
So...

38:40.465 --> 38:41.693
...why are you here?

38:42.667 --> 38:46.125
l have a month left on my insurance
and they pay up to six visits.

38:46.904 --> 38:49.532
l meant, is there a difficulty?

38:51.709 --> 38:52.733
Well....

38:55.113 --> 38:58.640
l'm sorry. l'm gonna go
because this is just stupid.

38:58.816 --> 39:00.841
Not that this is stupid. But l mean--

39:01.019 --> 39:04.682
Thank you for your time. Just for me,
you know. l mean, not this.

39:04.856 --> 39:07.188
-But thank you for understanding.
-All right.

39:07.358 --> 39:09.349
-Okay.
-Okay.

39:10.428 --> 39:13.420
You know, can l ask you
just one stupid question?

39:14.565 --> 39:15.589
No such thing.

39:15.767 --> 39:19.134
Because l'm leaving
and l'm not gonna do this again.

39:19.804 --> 39:23.968
l was wondering if there's one general
thing you've found over the years...

39:24.142 --> 39:26.372
...to be generally true...

39:26.544 --> 39:30.446
...in a general way
that would help anyone...

39:31.149 --> 39:32.776
...with any situation?

39:32.950 --> 39:34.975
That's a great question.

39:35.653 --> 39:37.211
Yes.

39:37.388 --> 39:41.848
l'd say, figure out what you want
and learn how to ask for it.

39:43.394 --> 39:44.986
Okay.

39:51.869 --> 39:53.530
Those are both really hard.

39:55.073 --> 39:59.271
Yes, but you came here,
which was hard for you.

39:59.444 --> 40:01.776
And you're leaving right away,
also hard.

40:01.946 --> 40:06.042
So you're tougher than
you think you are right now.

40:07.518 --> 40:09.008
Thanks.

40:09.454 --> 40:10.648
l appreciate that.

40:11.055 --> 40:13.615
-Good luck.
-Okay.

40:16.027 --> 40:18.757
-l can see why people do this.
-Thanks.

40:41.552 --> 40:44.680
l'm sorry. l thought some of them
were bringing their wives.

40:44.856 --> 40:48.690
That usually changes
the behavior considerably.

40:48.860 --> 40:52.956
The rookie who lives here had this,
maybe the best barbecue anywhere...

40:53.131 --> 40:54.689
...flown in from Houston.

40:54.866 --> 40:58.131
He bought a first-class seat
so his friend could fly it in.

40:58.302 --> 41:01.760
Wait till you taste it. Try the sauce
first. That's how you judge.

41:01.939 --> 41:05.272
-This place nails it. And you know--
-No hard feelings.

41:06.477 --> 41:10.038
You can stay, l just....
l can't do this right now.

41:12.150 --> 41:15.017
There's Christian athletes inside.
We'll eat with them.

41:15.520 --> 41:19.115
Do you ever wonder what's going on
in my life? Because you never ask.

41:19.624 --> 41:22.957
l thought l wasn't supposed to.
ls that just at night?

41:23.861 --> 41:27.422
This is-- You know what?
What l think l mean is...

41:27.598 --> 41:29.998
...l should tell you
what's going on with me.

41:35.907 --> 41:37.499
l got....

41:39.076 --> 41:41.169
Oh, God.

41:41.579 --> 41:43.046
l got cut.

41:43.681 --> 41:45.114
Sorry.

41:45.283 --> 41:49.276
Let's have some barbecue
and we'll talk about it. That's....

41:50.721 --> 41:52.052
l don't wanna eat now.

41:53.024 --> 41:54.753
l can't.

41:56.127 --> 41:57.992
You don't wanna eat anything?

41:58.162 --> 41:59.390
l just can't.

42:00.331 --> 42:01.923
Well....

42:04.836 --> 42:06.303
Okay.

42:07.238 --> 42:08.262
l'll go with you.

42:09.207 --> 42:10.231
Okay.

42:24.789 --> 42:27.758
So l'm gonna go
to grad school at night.

42:27.925 --> 42:31.793
l'll have to work a few jobs, but
l've got the private coaching thing...

42:31.963 --> 42:34.397
...and l lined up
this part-time retail thing.

42:34.565 --> 42:37.090
-That's great.
-That's good. l got that covered.

42:37.268 --> 42:39.532
l just have this problem
with my attitude.

42:39.704 --> 42:44.903
lt's like l have to get to the place where
l appreciate what the game gave me.

42:45.076 --> 42:49.479
And accept and even embrace
the obvious...

42:49.647 --> 42:52.343
...that the time comes
for every athlete when they--

42:52.516 --> 42:54.245
lt's never gonna come for me.

42:57.121 --> 42:59.112
You know what?
Maybe we shouldn't talk.

42:59.290 --> 43:01.258
Maybe we should watch TV
or something.

43:01.425 --> 43:04.986
No, no, no. Hold on, come here.

43:07.365 --> 43:09.094
l hear everything you're saying.

43:09.267 --> 43:14.330
Come sit over here. l'm gonna set you
down and make you something to eat.

43:14.505 --> 43:18.134
We get a little food in your stomach,
we'll both think better.

43:18.609 --> 43:21.373
You like inspirational stories?

43:21.545 --> 43:23.740
Okay, l got one for you.

43:23.915 --> 43:26.975
l knew a really good player once,
and the coach cut him.

43:28.219 --> 43:30.744
And the guy just felt....
He felt impotent.

43:30.922 --> 43:35.655
Now you're probably feeling whatever
the female version of that word is.

43:35.826 --> 43:36.850
lt's the same word.

43:38.596 --> 43:41.929
Don't let what's going on with you
make you give me a hard time.

43:42.099 --> 43:43.896
Because that's not productive.

43:44.068 --> 43:46.332
l'm not.
lt's the same word for women.

43:46.504 --> 43:48.404
''lmpotent''?

43:51.842 --> 43:54.242
Okay. Tie goes to the pretty one.

43:54.412 --> 43:58.041
Same word. He was feeling impotent,
just like you may be feeling.

43:58.215 --> 44:00.274
l don't think that's how l feel--

44:00.451 --> 44:01.816
Can l finish my thought?

44:01.986 --> 44:05.888
Maybe it'll help, maybe it won't,
but l'm trying.

44:07.058 --> 44:08.286
l'm sorry.

44:08.459 --> 44:10.188
-That's all right.
-Go ahead.

44:10.361 --> 44:15.230
Okay. So his girlfriend had a cat
and he started to save the cat's shit....

44:15.766 --> 44:18.428
-A little trust.
-Okay.

44:19.537 --> 44:24.167
He started to save all the cat's shit,
and every few days or so...

44:24.909 --> 44:29.209
...he'd take a little amount and wrap it
in a different package, like a gift...

44:29.380 --> 44:32.178
...or a magazine roll
or something you order online.

44:32.350 --> 44:34.318
Every few days for eight months...

44:34.485 --> 44:37.682
...he would send these cat turds
to the guy who cut him.

44:44.095 --> 44:45.653
ls that it?

44:47.064 --> 44:49.191
Yeah, that's it. lt's a great story.

44:49.367 --> 44:51.995
Did you understand it was the coach
he sent it to?

44:52.169 --> 44:56.299
To the guy who cut him?
He felt impotent, and then he....

44:56.474 --> 44:58.601
File it away. lt worked for this guy.

45:01.278 --> 45:04.213
No, so he stopped
when his anger went away--

45:04.382 --> 45:05.815
Yeah. Yeah.

45:05.983 --> 45:07.541
Well, the cat died.

45:09.887 --> 45:11.354
Oh, God.

45:11.522 --> 45:14.252
There, a smile.

45:14.625 --> 45:19.028
That's horrible.
l didn't know the cat was gonna die.

45:19.196 --> 45:20.390
You feel better.

45:20.564 --> 45:24.830
Great. l hated seeing you
touch bottom.

45:30.307 --> 45:31.535
That was sweet.

45:34.879 --> 45:36.904
Yeah, you're right.

45:39.884 --> 45:41.613
lt's okay.

45:52.797 --> 45:55.960
-You are amazing.
-You were great.

45:56.133 --> 45:59.364
-lt takes two, you know?
-At least.

45:59.670 --> 46:01.001
Creep.

46:03.541 --> 46:05.634
Oh, boy.

46:06.210 --> 46:09.373
You clap to bring on the lights
the minute we finish?

46:09.547 --> 46:11.344
Why? What's the matter?

46:12.083 --> 46:16.076
Just clapping your hands and
those dumb lights makes me feel like--

46:16.253 --> 46:19.780
Wait, wait, let me guess.
l think l can get it.

46:20.091 --> 46:22.457
Like l'm not thinking about you.

46:23.094 --> 46:24.721
Look who got it.

46:24.895 --> 46:27.921
-Yeah, look who read your mind.
-God.

46:28.099 --> 46:30.067
Yeah. What should l do?

46:31.135 --> 46:33.501
God. Turn them off!

46:34.738 --> 46:37.673
You wanna do it? Come on.
Oh, it's fun.

46:38.876 --> 46:40.639
Grow up.

46:41.112 --> 46:42.511
No.

46:47.518 --> 46:50.282
lt was kind of fun, wasn't it?

46:51.155 --> 46:53.851
l'm gonna teach you
how to have fun.

47:12.877 --> 47:14.401
-You didn't see that?
-What?

47:15.513 --> 47:18.744
Let me ask you something.
How do you know when you're in love?

47:20.217 --> 47:22.981
-lntriguing.
-Ryan. Get loose.

47:23.220 --> 47:24.687
Well....

47:27.191 --> 47:29.853
-What?
-l got a way.

47:30.027 --> 47:33.190
Whenever this one thing happens,
l know l'm done.

47:34.665 --> 47:37.361
lt's personal. l don't want
anyone making fun of me.

47:37.535 --> 47:39.560
No, no one's-- Go!

47:42.773 --> 47:46.675
l'm in love with somebody when
l wear a condom with the other girls.

47:49.547 --> 47:52.243
Holy shit, l'm in love.

48:06.197 --> 48:07.221
Hello?

48:07.565 --> 48:09.465
You up for a crazy idea?

48:09.633 --> 48:10.793
Yes.

48:10.968 --> 48:13.493
Maybe it'd be fun if you
kind of move in with me.

48:15.372 --> 48:16.703
<i>Hello? Are you there?</i>

48:16.874 --> 48:18.535
Barely.

48:19.743 --> 48:22.075
<i>-Are you serious?
-l know.</i>

48:22.546 --> 48:24.605
l told you it was crazy.

48:24.782 --> 48:27.114
Can you give me a minute
to form a thought?

48:27.284 --> 48:30.082
<i>-Yeah, yeah. Take your time.
-Okay. Thanks.</i>

48:30.254 --> 48:31.585
<i>Okay, l'll call you back.</i>

48:43.801 --> 48:45.132
That was quick.

48:45.302 --> 48:49.204
l know, but, Lisa, listen.
Today l caught myself--

48:49.373 --> 48:50.431
Thanks, Bobby.

48:51.842 --> 48:55.300
Today l caught myself wishing
you were in the bullpen with me.

48:55.479 --> 48:59.074
Literally having a daydream.
l mean, that's serious.

49:01.085 --> 49:02.848
<i>Li-- Are you there?</i>

49:03.020 --> 49:05.318
Hello? What are you doing?

49:05.723 --> 49:06.815
l think l'm thinking.

49:06.991 --> 49:10.256
Don't! You shouldn't have to think
about a great idea.

49:10.427 --> 49:12.361
You said this was a crazy idea.

49:12.529 --> 49:16.932
l know, l think it's both. l think part of
the greatness is how crazy it is.

49:17.101 --> 49:18.830
What first popped into your mind?

49:19.903 --> 49:23.031
That l don't know what to say
and it makes me feel stupid.

49:23.207 --> 49:24.333
Second thing.

49:24.508 --> 49:26.635
That l've never lived
with anyone before.

49:26.810 --> 49:29.540
Great. No one's had a chance
to ruin you.

49:31.315 --> 49:33.044
Have you ever lived with anybody?

49:33.217 --> 49:36.618
With me you get into what does
''living together'' mean...

49:36.787 --> 49:38.379
...and duration is a factor.

49:38.555 --> 49:40.716
<i>But listen, is--? Do you think...</i>

49:40.891 --> 49:43.951
...this is something...?
Do you wanna do this?

49:46.196 --> 49:48.494
<i>-Hello?
-l honestly....</i>

49:48.666 --> 49:51.066
-Yeah?
-l don't know how to figure this out.

49:51.635 --> 49:53.899
ls there tingling?
Do you have goose bumps?

49:54.071 --> 49:57.302
Maybe l need to work my voice
a little bit until you get them.

49:59.143 --> 50:00.405
l think l just got them.

50:02.046 --> 50:03.343
What?

50:03.614 --> 50:06.242
<i>-l think l just got them.
-Yeah.</i>

50:06.417 --> 50:08.044
l really like you, Matty.

50:08.252 --> 50:09.844
Okay.

50:11.021 --> 50:13.546
-Good phone call.
-Good phone call.

50:13.724 --> 50:15.817
<i>-Right? Yeah.
-Thank you.</i>

50:22.232 --> 50:24.223
This is such a mistake.

50:24.401 --> 50:27.700
-Overstepping alert.
-You sublet your apartment.

50:27.871 --> 50:32.109
You told me don't do anything halfway
unless you're willing to be half happy.

50:32.176 --> 50:36.044
Don't make important life decisions
when you are mush. lt's too dangerous.

50:36.213 --> 50:38.773
Fight low self-esteem,
don't give it the wheel.

50:38.949 --> 50:42.282
l am packed here. l am doing this.

50:42.453 --> 50:47.015
So back off, or do what you always do
for me, pull out some damn positives.

50:52.696 --> 50:54.254
l'm sorry, honey.

50:55.666 --> 50:57.099
Positives.

50:57.267 --> 51:00.703
Hell, the guy has
a 94-mile-an-hour fastball.

51:00.871 --> 51:03.704
He makes 1 4 million a year.
Go get him.

51:05.576 --> 51:08.374
-Got your bag? l cleared some space.
-Yeah, l just....

51:11.215 --> 51:13.150
-Yeah, come on in.
-Okay.

51:17.187 --> 51:20.122
Okay, l can get rid of
both of these things right here.

51:20.290 --> 51:23.589
l'll talk to the guys downstairs.
They have storage space.

51:23.761 --> 51:25.285
lt's okay.

51:25.729 --> 51:27.356
We'll make it work.

51:34.071 --> 51:35.504
Hey, boss, it's me.

51:44.081 --> 51:46.242
-Annie.
-Hi. Did you call that girl?

51:46.417 --> 51:51.753
No. You don't have to bring me food.
lt's enough that you found this place.

51:51.922 --> 51:55.323
That was selfish. You dress up
my neighborhood. Love your window?

51:55.492 --> 51:56.652
lt's great.

51:57.194 --> 51:58.218
This is--

51:58.395 --> 52:01.728
Cooking relaxes me when l can't
sleep. So why not just call her?

52:01.899 --> 52:04.561
Honestly? Because my
first impression wasn't great.

52:04.735 --> 52:07.135
l'd rather be more myself
when l see her next.

52:07.304 --> 52:09.795
What if someone beats you to her?

52:09.973 --> 52:12.874
Optimism is sanity for me right now.

52:14.044 --> 52:16.444
Please, sit down.
Make yourself comfortable.

52:16.613 --> 52:18.205
Relax.

52:20.918 --> 52:21.942
Look.

52:26.323 --> 52:27.847
l'm in a funny position...

52:28.025 --> 52:31.620
...but l know stuff about
what happened at work.

52:31.795 --> 52:34.525
l can't tell you
because of that thing l signed...

52:34.698 --> 52:39.897
...but if you start guessing, l can't help
it if this face is an open book. Look!

52:40.070 --> 52:44.302
Stop. You'd get in trouble, and just
listening could be wrongdoing for me.

52:44.475 --> 52:46.170
This information is killing me!

52:46.343 --> 52:49.642
lt's like l know someone is gonna
shoot you and l can't scream:

52:49.813 --> 52:53.977
''Watch out! That man's gonna
blow your frigging head off!''

52:54.151 --> 52:57.052
Please play this game with me,
or l'll just tell you!

52:57.221 --> 52:59.189
-No!
-For God's sake, let me unburden!

52:59.356 --> 53:03.190
Stop! Stop!
Annie, sit down, please. Sit down.

53:03.360 --> 53:07.421
Careful. You have to understand
what this is like for me right now.

53:07.931 --> 53:12.868
Picture a very angry ocean. A storm.
And l'm on this little tiny boat.

53:13.036 --> 53:16.096
And miraculously,
this boat is still afloat.

53:16.273 --> 53:19.140
And that boat is that
l haven't done anything wrong.

53:19.309 --> 53:23.177
Like letting you say something you're
legally constrained from revealing.

53:23.347 --> 53:27.249
Not doing anything wrong is
what's keeping me afloat. All right?

53:27.417 --> 53:29.612
lf l lose that, l'm gone.

53:32.089 --> 53:34.216
Don't rock the boat.

53:34.391 --> 53:36.359
-l know about the boat.
-Stop!

53:36.527 --> 53:40.190
-lt's a terrible boat! Get out of the boat!
-Respect me on this!

53:40.497 --> 53:42.590
For what it's worth, it doesn't matter.

53:44.635 --> 53:47.763
l think l've guessed
the same stuff you know.

53:48.605 --> 53:50.095
l think l know what you do.

54:06.924 --> 54:08.448
Nope.

54:09.459 --> 54:12.428
You couldn't function if you knew
what l'm talking about.

54:12.596 --> 54:14.689
Oh, l think l could.

54:15.866 --> 54:17.060
l think l am.

54:18.502 --> 54:20.493
-Leave it.
-What if l give you a hint?

54:20.671 --> 54:24.971
No, don't! Don't make me
leave my own apartment. Please.

54:32.716 --> 54:34.809
Okay. Eat something.

54:36.286 --> 54:37.776
Thank you.

54:39.289 --> 54:41.280
The lasagna looks amazing,
by the way.

54:48.332 --> 54:51.199
<i>-Hello, Dad.
-Are you coming to my place?</i>

54:51.668 --> 54:53.568
<i>-Almost there.
-Good.</i>

54:53.737 --> 54:57.002
<i>l have some disturbing news.</i>

54:57.174 --> 54:59.335
-What?
-l'll wait till you get here.

54:59.509 --> 55:02.444
Tell me. lt'd be nice to get
one piece of bad news...

55:02.613 --> 55:05.309
...without someone studying me
to see how l take it.

55:05.582 --> 55:08.346
Anger can be useful.
Watch out for the bitterness.

55:08.719 --> 55:09.845
What's the news, Dad?

55:13.557 --> 55:17.357
There are strong indications
that they are going to indict you.

55:17.794 --> 55:20.354
<i>l have canceled
everything l've got...</i>

55:20.530 --> 55:23.658
...and l am dedicating myself
completely to this.

55:26.036 --> 55:27.435
<i>George?</i>

55:54.931 --> 55:56.489
George?

55:59.636 --> 56:01.263
Oh, God, please don't kid me.

56:01.772 --> 56:02.830
How are you?

56:04.408 --> 56:06.137
Really....

56:08.045 --> 56:10.513
-Good to see you.
-Yeah.

56:11.248 --> 56:13.239
That's so funny.

56:19.256 --> 56:20.848
Thanks.

56:21.024 --> 56:23.185
-You didn't have to do that.
-Yeah, l did.

56:23.360 --> 56:25.590
So do you live in this building?

56:27.297 --> 56:29.128
Did you leave?

56:30.100 --> 56:31.397
Are you still here?

56:31.568 --> 56:32.626
Yeah. Absolutely.

56:33.570 --> 56:36.061
-Here l am.
-Okay.

56:36.606 --> 56:39.097
Sorry l'm not more hospitable.
l'm in a hurry.

56:39.276 --> 56:42.609
Can l go first?
l want to explain why l haven't called.

56:44.081 --> 56:45.878
l don't understand.

56:46.416 --> 56:50.978
l think l've made a bad assumption that
we've been on the same wavelength.

56:51.154 --> 56:54.055
That didn't come out right at all.
l didn't mean--

56:56.193 --> 56:58.559
l didn't quite mean to say that either.

56:58.929 --> 57:02.695
You ever wanna delete every sentence
you say, even as you say them?

57:02.866 --> 57:04.561
-No.
-No?

57:05.302 --> 57:09.005
You're funny. You know,
l'm really glad l ran into you.

57:09.072 --> 57:10.699
l bit your head off at dinner.

57:10.874 --> 57:14.742
l have this thing about rudeness,
so l'm glad l could say l'm sorry.

57:16.113 --> 57:17.137
-No--
-Lisa!

57:17.314 --> 57:20.112
Yeah! l'm in the kitchen!

57:21.585 --> 57:23.143
Hey, babe.

57:23.520 --> 57:25.988
George, this is my boyfriend, Matty.

57:28.291 --> 57:29.952
Nice to meet you.

57:31.695 --> 57:33.925
-Who is he?
-You didn't even say hello.

57:34.097 --> 57:37.533
l think you should check with me
before inviting some guy over...

57:37.701 --> 57:40.898
...so l'm a little too pissed off
to just say hello.

57:43.206 --> 57:44.833
Can l talk to you?

57:54.017 --> 57:57.077
-Why would l check with you?
-Want me to state the obvious?

57:57.254 --> 58:01.588
l have to check with you before inviting
someone up who carried our groceries?

58:01.758 --> 58:05.216
l didn't know about the groceries.
Maybe that changes things.

58:05.462 --> 58:06.895
l think it does.

58:07.063 --> 58:08.655
-Good talk.
-Wait. No.

58:08.832 --> 58:10.800
What's this obvious thing
l'm missing?

58:10.967 --> 58:15.165
Let's forget it. Otherwise, you want
me to put my foot in the trap? Okay.

58:15.338 --> 58:18.865
There's no trap. But let's show up
here. What am l missing?

58:19.176 --> 58:21.508
Okay. That this is my place.

58:24.047 --> 58:26.515
This is my place.

58:27.350 --> 58:29.147
Oh, boy.

58:32.722 --> 58:33.814
So long, Matty.

58:39.229 --> 58:40.890
Lisa, what are you doing?

58:41.064 --> 58:43.498
Congratulations,
you get your sock drawer back.

58:43.667 --> 58:47.034
Lisa, you can't do this.
We have a guest.

58:48.338 --> 58:51.501
Okay, you can have people over.
Without asking.

58:51.675 --> 58:53.870
You won't abuse the privilege. Right?

58:54.044 --> 58:57.571
There's also the safety issue,
which everyone's ignoring.

58:57.747 --> 58:58.873
Can you get the door?

59:11.695 --> 59:13.287
l think l screwed up.

59:13.463 --> 59:14.760
Not from my perspective.

59:14.931 --> 59:16.523
Yeah, thanks, buddy.

59:28.678 --> 59:30.111
Thanks.

59:31.882 --> 59:33.975
-Taxi?
-No, thanks, Tom.

59:34.150 --> 59:38.780
l just have to figure out
where l'm going.

59:46.496 --> 59:48.464
-Hey.
-Hey.

59:48.632 --> 59:51.328
Do you live around here?
l need to charge my phone.

59:51.501 --> 59:53.230
Yeah, l live pretty close.

59:53.470 --> 59:56.132
About an hour. By bus.

59:56.306 --> 59:57.671
l don't wanna mislead you.

59:58.208 --> 01:00:01.143
-Yeah. Okay.
-Okay.

01:00:02.045 --> 01:00:04.605
-Here.
-Thanks.

01:00:04.781 --> 01:00:06.749
-l'll take it. l got it.
-Thanks.

01:00:08.251 --> 01:00:10.583
lt's an hour 1 0, maybe.

01:00:16.760 --> 01:00:18.193
Hello, sir.

01:00:18.361 --> 01:00:20.591
Yes, she just came down.

01:00:20.764 --> 01:00:22.595
Okay, l'll try.

01:00:39.182 --> 01:00:42.549
Sorry, sir, l just wasn't able
to contact her for you.

01:00:59.035 --> 01:01:01.833
Man, so dead.

01:01:02.005 --> 01:01:05.202
lt's a new place.
l haven't totally unpacked yet.

01:01:05.375 --> 01:01:08.469
-Are you hungry?
-Lately? Always.

01:01:08.645 --> 01:01:10.510
Why are you asking?
You got nibbles?

01:01:10.714 --> 01:01:13.979
Oh, yes. Do you wanna hear a list?

01:01:17.287 --> 01:01:18.686
Lisa?

01:01:20.490 --> 01:01:23.653
l'm sorry, did you say something?
l was distracted.

01:01:23.827 --> 01:01:27.228
So was l. You wanna hear
a list of what l've got?

01:01:28.064 --> 01:01:31.090
-l'm not gonna be great company.
-Are you kidding me?

01:01:31.267 --> 01:01:35.499
This is the best conversation l've had
since the night we didn't talk.

01:01:36.940 --> 01:01:39.568
-Well, that's sort of funny.
-Flying start.

01:01:39.943 --> 01:01:42.173
Hey, what can l do to help?

01:01:48.118 --> 01:01:49.517
You make your own pot pie?

01:01:49.686 --> 01:01:54.180
A friend. Plates and silverware
are over here.

01:02:06.036 --> 01:02:07.867
Hello?

01:02:08.038 --> 01:02:10.529
lt doesn't matter where l am.

01:02:11.574 --> 01:02:12.871
You're gonna yell at me?

01:02:13.043 --> 01:02:16.171
That's it? That's why you called?
You know what l thin--

01:02:16.346 --> 01:02:17.779
Wait.

01:02:18.415 --> 01:02:20.576
You're gonna lose me.

01:02:24.254 --> 01:02:28.122
Just as well. lt wasn't gonna
go well from there anyway.

01:02:28.291 --> 01:02:30.384
l think we both need
some time to think.

01:02:33.196 --> 01:02:35.960
-Do you have any Guinness?
-l will get Guinness.

01:02:36.132 --> 01:02:38.032
-Don't go out of your way.
-No, no.

01:02:38.201 --> 01:02:42.160
l make a great drink, if you wanna
try it. lt's not an idle remark, l do.

01:02:42.338 --> 01:02:45.796
Okay. l'll try something.
Just not too strong.

01:02:46.476 --> 01:02:47.909
What am l doing?

01:02:48.078 --> 01:02:53.038
Stay honest with yourself when making
a mistake, there might be a takeaway.

01:02:53.917 --> 01:02:57.512
l'm gonna get drunk because
l'm too lame to stand how l feel.

01:02:57.787 --> 01:02:59.084
Great choice.

01:02:59.255 --> 01:03:01.223
-Could you do me a favor?
-Absolutely.

01:03:01.391 --> 01:03:03.689
And thank you for the opportunity.

01:03:04.494 --> 01:03:07.827
Could you not...?
l have a boyfriend, so could we just...?

01:03:08.531 --> 01:03:10.158
-Yes.
-Really?

01:03:10.467 --> 01:03:12.025
Yes.

01:03:12.502 --> 01:03:15.096
l have a teammate,
or an ex-teammate...

01:03:15.271 --> 01:03:19.674
...who says the only time l say anything
is when l drink Guinness, so watch out.

01:03:23.580 --> 01:03:26.947
Well, l think you've been saying a lot
without drinking.

01:03:27.117 --> 01:03:29.415
You are truly something.

01:03:29.886 --> 01:03:34.255
Which means my thinking about you
isn't just an aspect of the trouble l'm in.

01:03:34.424 --> 01:03:36.016
l don't follow you.

01:03:36.726 --> 01:03:38.694
-You're in some sort of trouble?
-No--

01:03:38.862 --> 01:03:42.161
First things first. l'll be right back.
Make yourself at home.

01:03:42.332 --> 01:03:43.765
Okay.

01:04:06.689 --> 01:04:08.054
Sorry.

01:04:11.394 --> 01:04:12.986
l got it!

01:04:13.897 --> 01:04:17.765
Okay, Lisa, if you're not back
in an hour, forget it. That's it.

01:04:17.934 --> 01:04:21.597
Okay, l'm removing the deadline.
Any time's good.

01:04:21.905 --> 01:04:23.167
l--

01:04:23.339 --> 01:04:26.706
l may have contributed
to the misunderstanding.

01:04:26.876 --> 01:04:30.710
l mean, if you could see my face,
you'd see how upset l am.

01:04:31.214 --> 01:04:32.943
Hold on, l'm gonna--

01:04:43.059 --> 01:04:45.027
No, let me....

01:04:48.431 --> 01:04:50.865
<i>Turn off the lights</i>

01:04:52.302 --> 01:04:53.870
<i>And light a candle</i>

01:05:05.548 --> 01:05:07.709
<i>Let's take a shower</i>

01:05:08.985 --> 01:05:11.249
<i>Shower together</i>

01:05:12.889 --> 01:05:15.380
<i>l'll wash your body</i>

01:05:15.592 --> 01:05:18.152
<i>You wash mine, yeah</i>

01:05:19.362 --> 01:05:23.958
<i>Rub me down
With some hot oils, baby</i>

01:05:30.840 --> 01:05:33.809
All right. l hope l haven't
built this up too much.

01:05:37.513 --> 01:05:40.846
-Okay. Tell me what you think.
-Oh, good.

01:05:45.588 --> 01:05:46.612
lt's good, right?

01:05:46.789 --> 01:05:49.121
-lt's delicious.
-Thanks. My own creation.

01:05:49.292 --> 01:05:53.752
l used to be a bartender, when l was
working my way through bartending.

01:05:56.599 --> 01:05:58.590
Oh, here. Please.

01:05:59.102 --> 01:06:02.094
